Rating: 3
Like a lot of other people, I found the basic recipe to be a good starting point, but on its own pretty dull. Here's what I added to give it a boost: 3 tbsp curry; 1tsp each of cumin, turmeric, and coriander; 2 tsp garam masala; 2 tbsp ketchup. The ketchup added some needed sweetness and savory. I suppose something else would also work, but ketchup happened to be at hand. I also threw in about 4 cups of baby spinach and used red lentils instead of yellow or brown.

Rating: 4
I kicked it up a few notches and it really rocked! I increased the curry (Red Curry) to 4 Tablespoons. Also I marinated 1.5 lbs of lamb in 3 Tbl of Curry and 3 Tbl of Oil over night in a zip lock bag. The remaining 1 TBL of Curry, I added to pot after adding the carrots. After cooking as directed for 1 hour, I also used a full box of frozen spinach and 1 full bag of frozen peas at last 10 minutes. After cooking, I let it cool down for 1 hours, then let it sit for 6 hours in refrigerator. Then just before serving, I set it back on stove and warmed it all up. Served it with Greek yogurt, and Garlic Naan, over rice. 5 Stars!

